                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.34/181: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-29T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>161. Your 279, June 22, 7 p.m.</p>
                <p>What interpretation does the Legation place on the statement “previous
                    discussions should be entirely canceled and the matter ended”? Is the Department
                    to understand that the Minister of Marine means that the “discussions” are ended
                    or that the contract, in the opinion of the Minister of Marine, has in any way
                    lapsed or been abrogated? Your further comment on the attitude of the Minister
                    of Marine regarding this point is desired by the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
